                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Recently someone I know got frustrated after grouping with an enchanter who (he says) could not pull for the life of him/her. Anyway, he posted his frustration, which got a conversation going about chanty pulling. Seeing that nobody who was talking about it was an enchanter, I threw my li'l two cents in.
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>I wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"><span style="text-decoration: underline">Spells I Use</span>:
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">(-)</span> <a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3199&amp;source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Arcane Rune</a>, 10m, Damage Absorber until the MT gains agro
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">(-)</span> <a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3197&amp;source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Pacification</a>, 9m, Self Explanatory (I hope!)
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">(-)</span> <a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=1702&amp;source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tashanian</a>, 1m, Pull (if this is used, I don't use Whirl 'til you Hurl)
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">(-)</span> <a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=303&amp;source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Whirl till you Hurl</a>, 1m, Pull (if this is used, I don't use Tashanian)
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">(-)</span> <a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3354&amp;source=Live" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sleep</a>, 6m (approx.), Mez'ing Adds
<br />

<br />
I try to always keep at least one MoB in camp in order to keep a constant flow of experience going--that means that I need to pull when the mob has anywhere from 60pct to 20pct HPs left. Assume it will take 20pct HPs to tash the MoB then run it to the camp. Add 20pct if: <span style="font-weight: bold">A</span> - I need to pac 2 or 3 mobs, <span style="font-weight: bold">B</span> - the group has high DPs, and/or <span style="font-weight: bold">C</span> - if I stun pull. I have never pulled a mob if the mob in camp has more than 60pct HPs left.
<br />

<br />
If I'm smart, I can get away with only one pacify before a single pull. Sometimes, however, it takes two or three. Then I tash or stun to pull the mob. I also rune myself every three pulls or so. However, all of that assumes that there is a decent tank who knows how to play their character in the group. Normally at this level that's not a problem. But sometimes the MT just <span style="font-weight: bold">can not keep agro</span>. When that happens, I end up casting rune on myself after every pull.
<br />

<br />
Let me give you an idea of how much mana I'm talking about.
<br />

<br />
Assume that in a LDoN every room I break in to is a room that's filled with five mobs, I'm in a high DPs group, and I have to pacify three of the mobs at break-in. That means every five mobs I spend 52m. 29m on the first pull and 10m on the second (I have to pac one of the final two mobs so they won't agro). Now I have three mobs left, and two are pacified. . .I can pull the fifth mob from the room then re-rune myself for 10m, then single the other two for 1m each. Of course, I'm assuming that no mobs from the next room agro, there are no roamers, <span style="font-weight: bold">and</span> the MT is decent.
<br />

<br />
I do not sit down to med until the mob's hps have hit 80pct due to the high agro of tash/stun. I get to med for 20pct HPs on the first mob, and 40pct HPs on the second, third, and fourth. That's about 28pct of the entire time that it takes to kill those mobs. I can use that time to regain all of my mana. However, I need every second of it.
<br />

<br />
Let's say the MT is crappy and I have to rune myself after every pull. I would end up spending and additional 40m. <span style="text-decoration: underline">Translation</span>: With a bad tank, I usually have to spend 92m every five pulls. When that happens I pull two or three mobs at a time then keep the adds mezd, or I just don't pull at all <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /> That saves a lot of mana <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" /> </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">So here are a couple questions</span>:
<br />
What can I do to improve my pulling? 
<br />
What are other good methods I can try when I pull?
<br />

<br />
Any input would be awesome  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Tras, 65 Chantress</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
