                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Is this on hard?  If not, you could save some mana by using Apathy instead of sleep.  Likewise, in areas with some room, you can save even more mana by using root instead of mez.  Saves some aggro too.
<br />

<br />
One thing that stands out is how much mana your spending, percentage-wise.  Arcane Rune is 400 mana.  I'd figure that a decently equipt 65 enchanter with Tranq up would have at least 4k mana.  With SCM and MP IV, that's down to 320.  Figure in specialization, it's a bit lower.  For it to take 10% of your mana pool indicates that either you have a very small mana pool or you are lacking SCM and/or MP IV.  If you are lacking either, getting them to reduce mana expenditures would be a good thing.  You don't mention FT either, obviously more FT means sitting to med is less important.  As a last note on mana savings, CA/LR and CS/ID both serve to make arcane rune last longer.  ER can help you save mana as well.
<br />

<br />
Duration of pacifies.  Do you have SCR1 or less?  If so, your pacifies last ~5 minutes.  So it shouldn't be necessary to pacify on the second pull.  If you have SCR2+, well, then you're out of luck.  Just don't rely on it staying this way.  Sooner or later, they'll fix it so Pacify will have it's proper duration.
<br />

<br />
Another way to cut down on your mana use and buy more med time is to not be the one pulling.  If you have a second melee in the group, make it their job to invite the actual mobs into camp.  Or a slower if you aren't the one slowing.  Skip the aggro so you can sit and med.  Don't have to do this all the time, just when you're a bit LOM.
<br />

<br />
From the sound of it, you're pulling intelligently, so that you cut out the mobs that would aggro and leave mobs far enough apart that you can pull them single without aggro'ing.  You can carry this one step further and once the mobs are far enough apart, don't pull.  Let's say you have a room of 5, and you've pulled 3, leaving one in the left near corner and one in the far right.  At this point, you should be able to move your group in to engage the left near and then the far right.  There's no reason to pull those.  If you fall into the 5 minute pacify category, you can go a step further with this and move in without pulling any mob in the room.  Just pacify the 3 in the middle and send the group in to kill the near left one.  Of course, if there are cleric mobs in the room, either they need to die first or you need to mez them.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
