                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Use recant magic or some other form of dispel magic to pull with. Mana cheap & removes buffs from mobs. All mobs in LDoN or any other zones are buffed, unless they have just spawned. If there is a shaman mob around, he'll sow, haste etc.. all the other mobs on his faction(I dont think mobs buff each other if they aren't social) that he comes within range off.
<br />
If you dont believe me, then try and charm a wizard mob, and then you can see with the new pet buff window that it has shield, DS manaskin and all sort of self buffs up  <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Also dispell is just 1 hate. Someone sitting on you inc with pull will get agro, so all a warrior has to do to peel mob off you, is shot an arrow or swing once on it. Safe for you and for the warrior since the mob wont be buffed(haste etc..)
<br />

<br />
Hope that helps, otherwise it looks ok. I usually dont pull ldon normal level. I just have the tank charge ahead where I just stand back and mezz the adds as they are on tank and once they move to cleric... cowardly maybe, but makes for fast adventures, and I use my mana on keeping a charmed mob up and nuking. Ofcourse single pull nameds tho.
<br />

<br />
As for hard level adventures, i've only had bards pull so far for my group. They can pre Mezz, pre slow etc.. I just park the mobs and add my DPS to group.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-style: italic">Coercer <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=219002" target="_blank" class="postlink">Trondur</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.kabald.org" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kabald</a>
