                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Root can be your friend where mobs are close, like in LDoN.
<br />

<br />
If there are 2 mobs within aggro range of each other, root one and the other will come after you.  Run back to camp.  Saves having to cast a spell on the mob you are pulling.  If there is a caster and a melee, root the melee for obvious reasons and take the caster first.
<br />

<br />
The root should wear off about when the first mob is done, and you don't therefore have to do anything to pull the mob.  If not, then the group moves to the mob.
<br />

<br />
If there are more than 2 in aggro range, selectively use pacify.
<br />

<br />
I like having a beastlord in the group as primary slower, helps a lot with the mana.  And having Spiritual Dominion for added mana regen helps. Also, Scryer's Trespass is really nice in LDoN with all the casters to tap.  And of course Necro's are a chanter's best friend with Mind Wrack Recourse.
<br />

<br />
My mana bar normally stays above 80% in LDoN even when I get 2-3 nukes in per mob.
<br />

<br />
Aallynth</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
