                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I used to pull with boggle until I heard some recommendations from people on this board to use recant/cancel magic.  I tried it as my main pull spell last night in Miragul's.  It worked better than boggle and I hade more mana.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" />   The key for me though, is getting the main tank to aggro the mob before it starts beating on the poor magician or wizard or necro.
<br />

<br />
I honestly think that the main tank can either make you look like the best puller in the universe, or make you look like a total newb.  And when the tank is really good... you can just keep multiples in camp, make sure tank has aggro on them then run and get more.  No mezzing unless you get an overpull.  
<br />

<br />
Most importantly though, I have learned that I have to communicate with the group beforehand and determine what the group expects on pulls.  If the puller and the group aren't on the same page, no spell lineup or special strategy is gonna work.
<br />

