                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As a chanter in Ldon, I started to get more and more bored as time went by because the pally always wanted to pacify pull.  So one day I said yah know what how about I pull?  So I loaded up pacify and Pacification and pulled up my lv 44 dispell magic.  Using these three spells I could effectively chain pull for my groups.  As mentioned above the Dispell magic generates very little agro, meaning all the MT has to do is attack the mob to get agro.  Even after rebuffing the group I very seldom get LoM using this technique, and there are always caster Mobs around somewhere to Tap  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" /> .
<br />

<br />
I have since carried this tactic outside of LDoN and use it in many different places.  being that I use to play a warrior who pulled all the time, I am quite happy to get back to doing it.  As I see it a chanter pulling is basically proactive crowd control.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
