                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My wife has problems thinking I need to be in charge and like a good wife likes to keep my eog in check.  Every time I read something here that looks cool that others do all the itme i want to try it.  Like charming or pulling, etc.
<br />

<br />
Well the Pally we typically group with likes to do the pulling and thinks its faster to pull 2-3 at a time.  But it is not very mana efficient for anyone.  So while he was on nights we did 3-4 LDoN groups and I went in telling people I was going to pull, and I got no arguments from my wife.  
<br />

<br />
Well, of course, it worked wonderfully.  We moved much faster.  I had the map so I knew where the traps were and we didn't sit in them as we usually do.  We had constant pulls.  On assassinations we pacified by single mobs to keep moving and avoid 1-2 mobs on the way to the big guy (or gal).  This is rather funny because I pull all the time in Bastion of Thunder for our groups, but LDoN pulling has been an issue.  But no more.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Spell lineup is:
<br />
Tash
<br />
Apathy
<br />
WoM
<br />
Greater Fetter
<br />
Tepid Deeds or Recant Magic (Necro to slow undead or a shaman in group)
<br />
NDT
<br />
Scyer's Tresspass
<br />
Pacify or Arcane Rune
<br />

