                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">When Ldon first came out I grouped up a lot with one of the warriors in my guild a lot and she pulled.  This was great fun mezzing all the MoBs she would bring and really helped hone in on my Mezzing skills.  Though as we progressed in levels and AoE mezz was no longer a viable option, I found it to be very dangerous to try and single mezz a hoard of MoBs without the tank taking a dive, or the healer getting womped on because he had to heal early.
<br />

<br />
So after that progression we starting using the Pallies to pull as they could pacify the under 55 mobs and I could mezz the smaller crowds of MoBs.  But this became very boring as I was not adding much of anything to the group, as our Nukes our Gimp along with our DoTs.  Sure I could keep the group augmented with mana and haste, but I felt as if I was being wasted.  Taking over the pulling myself and keeping a stream of Mobs coming in to be killed  has been the best option we have found to date.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=715917" target="_blank" class="postlink"> Majority Rulz </a>
