                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">On LDoN Adventures, I almost always pull for my groups.  I use whatever is efficient and fast.    On hard adventures, I'm alittle more careful, but still follow the same general ideas.
<br />

<br />
I use root as a primary means of crowd control.
<br />
I mez casters or mobs that get rooted too close together.
<br />
I use charm for both dps and as a pulling tool.
<br />
I am usually the slower for my group as well.
<br />

<br />
I can often pre-target into the next room while my group is still fighting the few I have rooted/slowed around the current room.  
<br />

<br />
Sometimes I'll just pull the mobs in with tash/slow and root them when they get to me.  If there are several in the next room, or if I can't tell how many are there, I'll usually pull with root.  At least that way, one mob is already contained, and the others comming in will only have assist agro on me; I'll move to corners in the room, and sit to encourage the mobs to come visit me, and I'll root them out of the way.
<br />

<br />
I also use my charmed pet to pull, as I have all the mobs in the current room usually rooted, and not mezed, I can tell my pet to attack them all, and he'll take them out one by one, usually going to the closest, sometimes to the weakest.  Most of the tanks I group with assist my pet, but even if they don't, I don't really care.  Anyway, I can target a mob in the next room, and send my pet to attack it, then I'll move back to the center of the room I'm in and sit.  This causes my pet to run into the next room and agro, usually pulling the mob he's after, and 2-3 (sometimes more) of his friends.  I can stand up, and provided the mobs are closer to my pet than they are to me, they'll all go back and jump him.   Only the mob that my pet is beating on will stay with the pet, the rest of them I can sit down and they'll come after me.
<br />

<br />
I split pulls, root mobs, and slow the entire room, usually keeping 5 or 6 mobs availalbe.   I also tell my groups that they can feel free to DoT non-caster mobs, as it'll take the group a couple minutes to get to all the mobs, this lets us take advantage of the mana efficiency of dots, and we can dot several mobs at once this way.
<br />

<br />
Normal adventures usually only take me 30 minutes tops, I think the fastest I've done was 17.  I have a pretty sizable mana pool, and gather mana, tho I rarely get low enough on mana to use it.
<br />

<br />
Some people cannot handle the pace that I set for LDoN groups, they get into cautious routines that are simple and boring... I don't know how they can do that day-in and day-out.  I was asked by one tepid cleric if I use pacification when I pull.. and I responded by saying, "No, I usually use AE tash".  I think she fainted.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378985" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tashim</a>, 65th Enchanter
<br />
<a href="http://www.drow.org/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Blood of the Spider</a>, <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Rathe</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
