                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I pull with a Blue Ceramic Band and Shiny Bob.  BCB is low enough agro that one smack with rune up and Shiny Bob can take over agro.  This normally means that he needs a Virtue or Focus, but it allows the tanks a couple more seconds between killing the last mob, and engaging the new one.  Plus, having the BCB in a inventory slot is nice to have an extra spell memmed.  
<br />

<br />
If I'm the slower, I'll slow around 90%.  I prefer to be in groups made up of a chanter, a cleric, and 4 melee.  Sometimes I won't even slow. I try to make sure that one is a bard or beastie for the extra mana regen.  Also, if there is a beastie, I'll let them slow.  Not only does this allow for some fast kills, but it also helps me out when int/cha aug or int caster gear drops  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
I have tried to charm a few times in LDoN (about 5 of 85ish missions).  If there is a shammy to slow and a bard to sing mana, I'm ok.  Even with cha at 270, I still seem to have trouble keeping a pet sometimes.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
