                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I generally tend to pull when I get fed up with the progress rate being too slow through Ldon.  My theory being that if theres a mob waiting to be killed the group is less likley to sit & have a chat before getting on with things!  
<br />

<br />
If I'm slowing then I'll pull with that (I do the same if I'm soloing too - I tend to take less of a beating otherwise), otherwise I tend to use tash.  In Ldon I wouldn't normally have any other debuff spells loaded (we need more spell slots!) 
<br />

<br />
My normal technique is to pull from maximum range & start casting mez or root soon as possible.  I prefer having it parked a little outside the group than getting the timing wrong & it beating on me.
<br />

<br />
Generally these days though I wouldn't bother slowing unless I'm in a pickup group - most of the guild groups have the mobs down to 25% by the time the spell has landed so I dont see the point.  Plus the fact they tend to go for the 'bulk purchase' pulling philosphy - if we bring 6 at once takes less running around - so I've generally got other things on my mind!</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=96863" target="_blank" class="postlink">Hardy - Coercer of Povar</a>
<br />
<a href="http://pub125.ezboard.com/bfuforcesunknown9695" target="_blank" class="postlink">Forces Unknown</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
